          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-07-17T17:57:35Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>End Congressional Stock Market Abuse Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 to prohibit Members of Congress from: (1) receiving a discounted&nbsp;purchase price or a premium sales price in a securities transaction, or (2) purchasing a&nbsp;nonpublic offering of a covered security available on a U.S. or foreign exchange.</p> <p>This prohibition shall not apply if the Member of Congress reasonably believes that the discount or premium was obtained in a manner generally available to the public.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-05-01T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <actionDate>2017-05-01</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
